Re: The Penultimate Japanese IME Guide... well, almost. :)
by Hyperworm » Thu 01.21.2010 7:43 pm I use Alt+` (left of 1 for me), which seems to switch back and forth between halfwidth and the previously selected mode (Hiragana, Katakana, ...).Except I need British keyboard layout, so I never type English with the IME in JP-mode (instead I Alt-Shift between that and EN). I only use Alt+` for moving from JP-alphanumeric to JP-Hiragana. Wish I didn't have to touch Alt+` at all; I have the Japanese IME set to start in Hiragana mode but it starts in alphanumeric anyway. o.0
